      "FacilityID": 1000080696,
      "SummaryText": "ACCIDENTAL RELEASE PREVENTION AND EMERGENCY RESPONSE POLICIES\n\n\n\nThis facility recognizes the hazards associated with the use of highly hazardous chemicals.  As a reflection of our policy to adhere to all applicable federal, state, and local laws and regulations, we submit this Risk Management Plan to address the hazards inherent with the use of ammonia, arsine, boron trichloride, chlorine, dichlorosilane, hydrogen chloride, hydrogen fluoride, hydrogen selenide, hydrogen sulfide, phosphine, sulfur dioxide, and trichlorosilane.  \n\n\n\nMatheson Tri-Gas, Inc. maintains a safety and environmental program, which is administered by the Director of Operations with assistance from Corporate Risk Management.  Our program addresses safety precautions regarding the handling of highly hazardous chemicals.  For example, written procedures have been developed for operating and maintaining the covered processes.  The company training policy requires all employees to be properly trained for a job position before assignment to that job.  The facility's maintenance program requires periodic inspections of process and safety equipment to ensure they are in good operating condition.  The overall safety and environmental program is geared towards the prevention of an accidental release at the facility.  The program also incorporates emergency procedures to mitigate the effects of a release if it does occur.  At such an event, trained personnel will assess the situation and notify the emergency response team and outside responding agencies as necessary.    \n\n\n\nSTATIONARY SOURCE AND REGULATED SUBSTANCES\n\n\n\nMatheson Tri-Gas, Inc. manufactures industrial grade gases and trans-fills into compressed gas cylinders of varying sizes.  The business is located at 1700 Scepter Road in Waverly, Tennessee.  The regulated substances maintained at the facility are ammonia, arsine, boron trichloride, chlorine, dichlorosilane, hydrogen chloride, hydrogen fluoride, hydrogen selenide, hydrogen sulfide, phosp"
    },
